/* Create an Integer variable called time and assign a value to it.
   If the value is greater than 6 → print “Good Morning”.
   If the value is less than 6 → print “Good Night”.
*/

Integer time1 = 5;    // for getting present time to pass to integer Datetime.now().hour()   
if(time1 > 6){
    System.debug('Good Morning');
}else{
    System.debug('Good Night');
}

/*
Declare a variable isMine of type Boolean (declare only, no assignment).
   Write a condition that prints:
     “Yes” → if isMine is true
     “No” → if isMine is false
     “MayBe” → if isMine is not equal to any of them.
*/

Boolean isMine; // This is null by default

if(isMine == true){
    System.debug('Yes');
}else if(isMine == false){
    System.debug('No');
}else{
    // This runs because isMine is null
    System.debug('MayBe');
}

/*
Take three subject marks in three different variables and handle these cases:

   1. If the total marks exceed 75% and all individual subject marks are greater than 75 → print “Excellent Performance”.
   2. If total > 75% but any individual mark < 75 → print
      Good Performance
      You need to improve on <subject>
   3. If total < 75% → print
      Bad Performance
      You need a lot of improvement
      
   4. Unit test by changing values of the subject marks.
*/

// 1. Initialize variables with subject marks
Integer math = 90;
Integer science = 50;
Integer english = 90;

// 2. Calculate the total and percentage
// We divide by 300.0 to tell Apex to treat this as a Decimal calculation
Decimal totalMarks = math + science + english;
Decimal totalPercentage = (totalMarks / 300.0) * 100;

// 3. Logic Handling
// Check if total is > 75% AND every individual subject is > 75
if (totalPercentage > 75 && math > 75 && science > 75 && english > 75) {
    System.debug('Excellent Performance');
} 
// Check if total is > 75% but the condition above failed
else if (totalPercentage > 75) {
    System.debug('Good Performance');
    
    // Check each subject individually for specific feedback
    if (math < 75) {
        System.debug('You need to improve on Math');
    }
    if (science < 75) {
        System.debug('You need to improve on Science');
    }
    if (english < 75) {
        System.debug('You need to improve on English');
    }
} 
// If the total percentage is 75 or below
else {
    System.debug('Bad Performance');
    System.debug('You need a lot of improvement');
}
